pve-fclu (0.1.0~alpha2) stable; urgency=medium

  * pve-fclu-hitachi: re-ship the web UI + host-side extras dropped in the
    alpha1 rename swap, so the driver package is at parity with the superseded
    pve-storage-hitachiblock for the GUI and PR paths:
    - The ExtJS storage panel (src/www/manager6/hitachiblock.js, served as
      /pve2/js/pve-fclu-hitachi.js): the "Add: Hitachi Block" create/edit dialog
      and the friendly grid label. Wired into index.html.tpl via postinst +
      an interest-noawait dpkg trigger (re-injected on pve-manager upgrades),
      removed on package removal via prerm; `make install` does the same for
      source installs. Fields track the plugin's properties()/options().
    - The opt-in SCSI-3 PR systemd units (qemu-pr-helper.socket/.service),
      installed DISABLED (dh_installsystemd --no-enable --no-start); enable the
      socket per node only when using persistent_reservations.
    - storage.cfg + multipath config examples under the package doc dir.
    Still deferred: the hitachiblock-repl replication CLI (it is coupled to the
    reference's old module layout and needs a rewrite against the FCLU internals).

 -- Ciro Iriarte <ciro.iriarte+software@gmail.com>  Wed, 01 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0300

pve-fclu (0.1.0~alpha1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial packaging of the vendor-neutral FCLU storage framework as a
    multi-binary source package (ARCHITECTURE.md §11):
    - pve-fclu-core: the generic PVE storage plugin base, the volname->LU
      registry, the credential store, the capability model, the abstract
      driver contract (Provides: fclu-driver-api-1), and the FC multipath host
      connector. Names no vendor.
    - pve-fclu-hitachi: the Hitachi VSP driver + Configuration Manager REST
      transport + the thin type()='hitachiblock' plugin. Depends on
      pve-fclu-core (= ${binary:Version}) and the fclu-driver-api-1 contract.
      Provides/Replaces/Conflicts the standalone pve-storage-hitachiblock so an
      upgrade swaps cleanly and existing type: hitachiblock storage.cfg entries
      keep working verbatim.
    - pve-fclu: optional convenience metapackage (Depends core, Recommends the
      packaged vendor drivers).
    Pure Perl; the unit suite (164 tests) runs at build time via dh_auto_test.
    FCLU/Driver/Mock.pm is the test-only reference driver and is not shipped.
  * UPGRADE NOTE: replacing pve-storage-hitachiblock is a clean data-path swap —
    the type: hitachiblock storage plugin and its multipath data path are
    preserved — but because pve-fclu-hitachi Conflicts the old package, apt
    removes it wholesale. This alpha does NOT yet re-ship the old package's
    extras: the ExtJS GUI add/edit panel, the hitachiblock-repl CLI, and the
    opt-in SCSI-3 PR (qemu-pr-helper) systemd units. Storage keeps working via
    storage.cfg + pvesm/API; the web-UI edit dialog and those helpers return in
    a later slice. Configure/verify storage from the CLI until then.

 -- Ciro Iriarte <ciro.iriarte+software@gmail.com>  Wed, 01 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0300
